# Auth & Permissions

Better Auth is configured in `packages/auth/src/auth.ts` (exported as `auth` from `@repo/auth/auth`) with the `admin` plugin. Sessions are persisted in PostgreSQL via Drizzle — the schema lives in `packages/db/src/schema.ts` (`user`, `account`, `session`, `verification` tables).

## Reading the session server-side
Call `auth.api.getSession({ headers: await headers() })` (see `apps/web/src/app/(dashboard)/layout.tsx`). The dashboard layout redirects to `/login` when there is no `session.user.role`.

## Adding a protected route
1. Read the session server-side as above.
2. Redirect unauthenticated users to `/login`.
3. For admin-only pages, check `session.user.role` before rendering.

## Roles
Two roles (`admin` / `user`) come from the Better Auth `admin` plugin and live on `session.user.role`. On the server, gate tRPC procedures with `adminProcedure` / `userProcedure` from `packages/api/src/middleware/rbac.ts` — gate by role, not by user id.
